Check out the first two episodes of the series for free, only on @kartoonchannel!: https://www.kartoonchannel.com/shows/superhero-kindergarten

node.text: In 2002, Stan Lee was honored with the Life Career Award from the Saturn Awards. And this year, Stan is getting an award named after him! The inaugural Stan Lee World Builder Award will be presented on the first EVER live stream of the Saturn Awards next Friday the 13th at 6pm PT / 9pm ET! Tune in to see the biggest names in TV and film – for more info go to www.saturnawards.com @saturnawards #saturnawards #flashbackfriday

node.text:
A man of many talents: Not only did Stan pen stories, he wrote song lyrics, too! 
While serving in the military during WW2, Stan was sent to the Army Finance Department to create a training manual for them. There, he saw the accountants marching – without music! So, he decided to write a marching jingle for them to the tune of the Air Force Song. 
In honor of #WorldMusicDay, please enjoy this candid moment of Stan breaking out in song in his office in 2012.

node.text:
From a hot dog vendor to a crazy barber and everything in between, Stan relished the chance to play an array of characters over the years.

Superhero Kindergarten, one of the final projects he worked on, pays homage to Stan the Cameo King and his humor with a new cameo to discover in every episode –and true to Stan's stories, it’s fun for all ages!

Have you spotted all his characters? If not, catch up with the series on @kartoonchannel! at kartoonchannel.com.

#StanLee #SuperheroKindergarten #KartoonChannel
